          <xs:documentation>Indicates how to interpret the Quantities:
= indicates an exact strength
+/- indicates an approximate strength
>, >=, &lt;, &lt;= indicate a minimum or maximum (inclusive) strength
Between indicates a value between the two given quantities
					</xs:documentation>
        </xs:annotation>
      </xs:element>
      <xs:element name="Quantity" type="core:QuantityType">
        <xs:annotation>
          <xs:documentation>The base strength of the active ingredient.</xs:documentation>
        </xs:annotation>
      </xs:element>
      <xs:element name="SecondQuantity" type="core:QuantityType" minOccurs="0">
        <xs:annotation>
          <xs:documentation>If the operator is Between, this is the upper bound of the strength range of the active ingredient. For the other operators, this Second Quantity indicates a concentration: the amount or volume of the product that contains the strength in the Quantity element.</xs:documentation>
        </xs:annotation>
      </xs:element>
    </xs:sequence>
  </xs:complexType>
</xs:schema>
